1. Introduction

The External Track & Trace system is built on a data-driven architecture, where most of the business logic is controlled through database tables instead of hardcoded logic.

This design makes the system:

Flexible

Scalable

Easy to maintain


The database plays a critical role in:

Storing transaction data

Driving XML generation

Controlling integration behavior

Maintaining history and audit logs



---

2. Data Model Overview

The system consists of three main categories of tables:


---

2.1 Core Business Tables

These tables store the actual transaction data.

DPW_EVENT

DPW_REQUEST



---

2.2 Track & Trace Tables

These tables store integration-related data.

DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_AND_TRACE

DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_AND_TRACE_HISTORY

DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_AND_TRACE_HISTORY_AUD



---

2.3 Mapping Table

This is the most critical table:

DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_TRACE_MAPPING


It controls how data is transformed and sent to Connexis.


---

3. DPW_EVENT Table (Core Table)

The DPW_EVENT table is the central table of the system.


---

Purpose

Stores event-level transaction data

Acts as the main source for:

XML generation

Status tracking

Integration processing




---

Important Fields

Field	Description

EVENT_ID	Unique identifier of the event
CONNEXIS_REQ_REF_ID	Reference ID from Connexis
CONNEXIS_REQ_TNX_ID	Transaction ID from Connexis
CONNEXIS_STATUS	Current status (Ready, Sending, ACK, NACK)
PROD_CODE	Product code
TNX_TYPE_CODE	Transaction type
SUB_TNX_TYPE_CODE	Sub transaction type
PROD_STAT_CODE	Product status
EB_CUS_FLAG	Customer eligibility flag
EB_CUS_ID	Customer ID
EB_BAN_ID	Bank identifier



---

Why This Table is Important

All major operations such as:

XML generation

Status updates

Integration checks


are driven from this table.


---

4. DPW_REQUEST Table

The DPW_REQUEST table stores request-level data.


---

Purpose

Stores high-level transaction details

Linked with events



---

Key Point

Although both request and event exist: 👉 Tracking is done at event level, not request level


