7. Mapping Table (Core Logic Engine)

Table: DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_TRACE_MAPPING


---

Purpose

This table is the brain of the system.

It defines:

How Conserto statuses map to Connexis

What values should be sent in XML

What action should be triggered



---

Columns

Column	Description

BRANCH_CODE	Branch identifier
COUNTRY_CODE	Country
PGPE_CODE	Product group
ACTION	Action type (Validate, AutoIS, etc.)
STATUS_CST	Conserto status
STATUS_CXT	Connexis status
PROD_CODE	Product code
TNX_TYPE_CODE	Transaction type
SUB_TNX_TYPE_CODE	Sub transaction type
PROD_STAT_CODE	Product status
TNX_STAT_CODE	Transaction status



---

8. How Mapping Works (Very Important)

When an event is processed, the system performs:


---

Step 1: Read Current Data

Current event status

Action performed (e.g., Validate)



---

Step 2: Query Mapping Table

SELECT * FROM DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_TRACE_MAPPING
WHERE STATUS_CST = current_status
AND ACTION = current_action;


---

Step 3: If Mapping Found

The system extracts:

Connexis status (STATUS_CXT)

Product code

Transaction type

Other required fields



---

Step 4: Use Mapping Data

This data is used to:

Generate XML

Decide whether to send data

Control workflow execution



---

If Mapping Not Found

Process stops

No XML is generated



